# Docs / PRD maintenance

`docs/PRD.md` is the **requirements source of truth** for the slide product.

## When editing

- Keep goals, non-goals, and acceptance criteria aligned with a slides-only repo
- Do **not** move facilitator artifacts (agenda, timing, speaker notes, prep, Q&A banks) into “in repository” deliverables
- Brand tokens and assets (§8) and the links checklist (§6) stay authoritative — if they change, update matching `.cursor/rules` files
- Prefer precise requirement language over workshop prose or slide copy

## Consistency checks

- In-repo vs out-of-repo lists must stay mutually exclusive
- Learning outcomes and must-cover topics must remain achievable from slides alone
- Do not invent new brand systems or purple/AI aesthetics in brand requirements
